I"<p>This is the text for the post. It won’t be used as the excerpt as it will use the custom summary set in the post instead.</p>

<p>If the summary is not set it will use the default excerpt generated by Jekyll.</p>

<p>To use a custom summary, set the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">summary</code> in the post’s front matter.</p>

<div class="language-yaml highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="na">layout</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">post</span>
<span class="na">title</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">Example post with a summary</span>
<span class="na">summary</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="pi">|-</span>
    <span class="s">This is the custom summary for the post.</span>

    <span class="s">It can be in **markdown format** if required.</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
